## SUITE IMPLEMENTATION PLANNING AREAS

### Risk Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Prevent over-risking and drawdown breaches while reducing manual calculation errors.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
Risk %, max daily loss, account equity, broker lot step/min lot, current spread.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Lot size calculator UI, max-loss warning, trade-block state when limits exceed, risk-evaluation logs.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
Must respect per-broker position sizing rules and prop daily/max drawdown limits.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
Risk engine, account snapshot service, broker symbol-spec module.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
If symbol spec unavailable, fallback to safe minimum lot and warning banner.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
Given fixed inputs, calculated lot size matches expected output within precision rules.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`risk_calc_requested`, `risk_calc_completed`, `risk_block_triggered`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha internal validation with multiple brokers, beta with selected users, stable after support tickets < threshold.

### Execution Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Speed up trade management while preventing accidental rule-violating actions.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
Order action intent, open positions, broker execution rules, spread/volatility state.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Action buttons, confirmation states, execution status toasts, audit trail entries.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
No execution action can bypass guard checks; must timeout safely on slow broker response.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
Execution gateway, guard middleware, broker adapter.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
On rejected modification, revert UI state and provide reason code + retry option.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
SL/TP/partial-close actions produce correct broker payload and post-state reconciliation.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`exec_action_requested`, `exec_action_rejected`, `exec_action_confirmed`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha feature-flagged controls, beta partial rollout, stable after broker compatibility matrix passes.

### Session Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Keep traders aligned with valid sessions and avoid poor-liquidity windows.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
Timezone settings, session templates, spread, rollover windows.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Session clock HUD, session-open/close alerts, session-based trade gating state.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
Session logic must remain accurate across DST/timezone transitions.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
Session calendar module, time service, spread feed.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
If time source desync detected, fallback to local clock and show drift warning.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
Session transitions trigger exactly once per configured boundary.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`session_state_changed`, `session_guard_blocked`, `clock_drift_detected`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha on major symbols only, beta with timezone edge-case monitoring, stable after DST validation cycle.

### Prop Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Reduce prop-rule breaches and improve challenge completion reliability.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
Rule profile, account equity/drawdown, daily P/L, position exposure, trading window.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Rule status dashboard, hard-stop alerts, account lock/soft lock state, violation logs.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
Strictest prop rule always wins; no hidden override path in public versions.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
Rule engine, account state service, challenge progress tracker.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
If rule profile incomplete, switch to conservative default profile and require user confirmation.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
Known violation scenarios always produce pre-trade block and post-event record.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`prop_rule_loaded`, `prop_rule_blocked_trade`, `prop_violation_prevented`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha internal with synthetic scenarios, beta with multiple prop templates, stable after scenario suite reaches 100% pass.

### Dashboard Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Provide at-a-glance operational clarity with minimal click depth.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
User widget config, account KPIs, active symbol state, session/guard status.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Dashboard cards/widgets, status badges, quick alerts, layout state persistence logs.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
Must remain responsive under high event volume; render fallback placeholders when data missing.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
UI component library, telemetry stream, state store.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
If one widget fails, isolate error and keep remaining dashboard operational.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
Dashboard first paint and critical status cards render within agreed performance budget.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`dashboard_loaded`, `widget_render_failed`, `layout_updated`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha with core widgets, beta with extension widgets, stable after UI performance and crash thresholds met.

### Analytics Suite — IMPLEMENTATION SPEC
#### Objective (user problem + value)
Turn trading activity into actionable review data with low export friction.

#### Inputs (manual, broker, account, session, market)
Trade history, execution metadata, account snapshots, optional user tags/notes.

#### Outputs (UI elements, alerts, state changes, logs)
Export controls, performance summary charts, completed-export notifications, processing logs.

#### Constraints (prop limits, broker variation, latency, offline behavior)
Exports must normalize broker field differences and avoid blocking primary trading workflows.

#### Dependencies (shared modules + external services, if any)
Trade history service, normalization layer, export formatter.

#### Failure modes + fallbacks
If export format fails, fallback to raw CSV with explicit schema notice.

#### Acceptance criteria (testable)
Exported files pass schema checks and match on-screen summary totals.

#### Telemetry/events (what to log)
`export_started`, `export_completed`, `export_failed`, `analytics_view_opened`.

#### Versioning/release policy (alpha/beta/stable)
Alpha for internal journaling, beta with external user samples, stable after export compatibility verification.

